The AA said on Monday a litre of petrol was likely to set you back 56 cents more next month, while its predicting that diesel will decrease by 5 cents. JOHANNESBURG - The Automobile Association (AA) is warning cash-strapped consumers to expect yet another fuel price hike, due to higher international prices. The AA said on Monday a litre of petrol was likely to set you back 56 cents more next month, while its predicting that diesel will decrease by 5 cents. If the predictions are correct, it would be the third consecutive hike this year.